                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3959ct64/manifest/annotation/p3",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>with that devotion necessary for the recital of<lb/> our sublime\n                                        ritual, it gives the high min-<lb/>ded adult a distaste for\n                                        the service, now<lb/> contrast our service with that of the\n                                        gentiles<lb/> only see how decorous every part of their<lb/>\n                                        service is performed. When you enter into<lb/> some of their\n                                        churches we are struck with<lb/> awe we are reminded often\n                                        with the solemn<lb/> scriptural injunction of “the Lord is\n                                        in this<lb/> holy Temple let all the earth keep\n                                        si-<lb/>lence before Him.”</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">There must be something done to stimu-<lb/>late\n                                        this lukewarmness existing amongst<lb/> our Co-religionists,\n                                        had I but the power<lb/> to <sic>weild</sic> the pen and\n                                        give vent my fee<lb/>lings in this matter.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I am aware that any attempt to ab-<lb/>ridge our\n                                        form of service would meet<lb/> with opposition at first,\n                                        but as it is<lb/> not the old mosaic or Temple form of<lb/>\n                                        service I see no good reason why the<lb/> change cannot be\n                                        made to suit the<lb/> country &amp; times in which we live.\n                                        I wish we<lb/> had but one minhag in\n                                                  <placeName>America</placeName>, and the<lb/>\n                                        service read in good grammatical Hebrew,<lb/> any thing that\n                                        I in my feeble efforts can<lb/> effect, God knows I am\n                                        willing to<lb/> do, hoping to hear soon. I remain yours\n                                        &amp;c</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(9)\">\n                                        <persName role=\"author\">Jacob Ezekiel</persName>\n                              </p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3959ct64/canvas/p3"
                }
              ]
